<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - Meritor Transfer Cases MTC-4208, -4210, and -4213 - Power
        Take-Off (PTO) - Install Optional Indicator Switch
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Install Optional Indicator Switch</title>
        <para>You must install the optional PTO switch listed in the Table below.</para>
        <table id="t1303504">
            <title>PTO Switch Option</title>
            <tgroup cols="4">
                <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.26*"/>
                <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="0.68*"/>
                <colspec colname="col3" colwidth="0.95*"/>
                <colspec colname="col4" colwidth="1.12*"/>
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Part Name</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Qty.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Part Number</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Description</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Switch and Connector Assembly</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>1</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>3237-W-1167</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>2 Amp x 12 VDC, M16 x 1" thread</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the screw and washer from the end of the PTO cap (Figure 64).</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply Loctite&#174; 518 gasket sealant to the indicator switch threads.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the indicator switch. Tighten the switch to 25-30 lb-ft (34-41 Nm) (Figure 65).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1303564" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303564.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
            <caption>Figure 64. Remove Screw and Washer</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. OPTIONAL CONNECTOR SWITCH ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                <callout1>2. AIR CONTROL PORT</callout1>
                <callout1>3. SWITCH PORT SCREW AND WASHER</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1303565" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303565.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
            <caption>Figure 65. Install Indicator Switch</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. OPTIONAL CONNECTOR SWITCH ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                <callout1>2. SPECIAL PLUG AND WASHER</callout1>
                <callout1>3. AIR CONTROL PORT</callout1>
                <callout1>4. INDICATOR SWITCH</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
